channel.title: First competitive match in CS:GO
channel.description:
[url]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5jgHVPbkJfU[/url]
America VS Europe.
I am a big fan of CS series, and GOD THEY GOT RID OF TAPPING.
That means no more crazy AR shots like they did.
However, they still put in the quickscopes, making the sniper rifles very versatile, yet expensive to use.
I kinda like this, and not like this at the same time.
What are your opinions?

item.dc:creator: Surplus
item.description:
Well to be honest, judging by how many people never switched to Source and stuck with 1.6 I think valve is perfectly fine in their fear.

Also although CS is technically another modern based shooter, it manages to have a very unique feel in its pacing and gameplay. I think if they tried to change it they’d just end up making more bland.
